## ApiSources-T3 [G3] Model-First Agent Configuration Tests
**Status:** done
**Priority:** P0
**Test File:** `backend/src/relay/config.rs` (inline `#[cfg(test)] mod tests`, lines 682–862)
**Module:** `backend/src/relay/config.rs`, `frontend/src/views/AgentsConfigView.vue`
**Tags:** stack:backend, stack:frontend, module:api-sources, type:unit
**Depends on:** ApiSources-G3, ApiSources-D1, ApiSources-P3

### Verification Summary (Quinn — draft-tests)

All 15 backend tests implemented inline in `config.rs`. Code review confirms implementation matches design spec. One cosmetic CSS deviation noted (non-blocking). Frontend verified via code review.

### Test Cases (all implemented, all passing)

| TC | Description | Status |
|----|-------------|--------|
| TC-T3.1 | resolve_model with valid model_id returns correct model | ✅ |
| TC-T3.2 | resolve_model with invalid model_id falls back to first model | ✅ |
| TC-T3.3 | resolve_model with empty model_id falls back to first model | ✅ |
| TC-T3.4 | resolve_model with missing api_source_id falls back to first source | ✅ |
| TC-T3.5 | resolve_model returns None when no api_sources | ✅ |
| TC-T3.6 | resolve_model returns None when source has empty models | ✅ |
| TC-T3.7 | assign_model_ids migrates tier to model_id | ✅ |
| TC-T3.8 | assign_model_ids falls back to first model when tier not found | ✅ |
| TC-T3.9 | assign_model_ids skips configs that already have model_id | ✅ |
| TC-T3.10 | assign_model_ids handles empty api_sources | ✅ |
| TC-T3.11 | Serde round-trip — old JSON (no model_id) deserializes with defaults | ✅ |
| TC-T3.12 | Serde round-trip — new JSON (with model_id) deserializes correctly | ✅ |
| TC-T3.13 | Serde round-trip — new JSON without model_tier uses default | ✅ |
| TC-T3.14 | generate_default_agents_with_source produces empty model_id | ✅ |
| TC-T3.15 | resolve_model preserves all AgentConfig parameters in ModelConfig | ✅ |

### Coverage Matrix

| G3 Goal | Tests |
|---------|-------|
| AgentConfig stores model_id | TC-T3.11, TC-T3.12, TC-T3.13, TC-T3.14 |
| Model tier becomes display tag only | TC-T3.7, TC-T3.8 (tier used only for migration lookup) |
| Frontend model list per ApiSource | Verified via code review |
| resolve_model() by model_id (no tier walk) | TC-T3.1–T3.6, TC-T3.15 |
| Default configs reference model_id | TC-T3.14 |
| Migrations convert tier→model_id | TC-T3.7–T3.10 |

### Frontend Verification (Code Review)

- ✅ `AgentConfigDto` has `model_id: string` and `model_tier` for display
- ✅ `useApiSources.ts` exports `getModelsForSource(sourceId)` helper
- ✅ `AgentsConfigView.vue` model selector lists all models from selected ApiSource with tier badges
- ✅ Watcher on `api_source_id` auto-selects first model + updates model_tier
- ✅ Watcher on `model_id` syncs model_tier from selected model
- ✅ i18n: uses `t('agents.model')` for label
- ✅ No duplicate definitions

### Cosmetic Deviation (Non-blocking)

Tier badge CSS uses subtle/low-opacity backgrounds (better for dark mode) instead of spec's bold solid backgrounds. Hue values match spec exactly: Min=gray, Lite=green, Mid=blue, Pro=purple, Max=amber.

### Bugs Found

None.

### Test Code Location

All Rust tests: `backend/src/relay/config.rs` → `#[cfg(test)] mod tests` → functions `test_resolve_model_*`, `test_assign_model_ids_*`, `test_serde_*`, `test_generate_defaults_empty_model_id`, `test_resolve_model_preserves_parameters`

