### Coverage Matrix

| G3 Goal | Tests |
|---------|-------|
| AgentConfig stores model_id | TC-T3.11, TC-T3.12, TC-T3.13, TC-T3.14 |
| Model tier becomes display tag only | TC-T3.7, TC-T3.8 (tier used only for migration lookup) |
| Frontend model list per ApiSource | Verified via code review (see below) |
| resolve_model() by model_id (no tier walk) | TC-T3.1, TC-T3.2, TC-T3.3, TC-T3.4, TC-T3.5, TC-T3.6, TC-T3.15 |
| Default configs reference model_id | TC-T3.14 |
| Migrations convert tier→model_id | TC-T3.7, TC-T3.8, TC-T3.9, TC-T3.10 |

### Implementation Verification (Backend)

- ✅ `AgentConfig` struct has `model_id: String` with `#[serde(default)]`
- ✅ `model_tier: ModelTier` kept with `#[serde(default)]` as deprecated field
- ✅ `resolve_model()` uses direct `model_id` lookup, no tier downgrade walk
- ✅ `assign_model_ids()` migrates empty model_id from tier, returns bool for dirty tracking
- ✅ `generate_default_agents_with_source()` generates empty model_id (filled by migration)
- ✅ `load_or_generate_agent_configs()` calls `assign_model_ids()` and saves only when dirty
- ✅ All 15 test cases implemented inline in `#[cfg(test)] mod tests` block

### Implementation Verification (Frontend)

- ✅ `AgentConfigDto` has `model_id: string` and `model_tier` for display
- ✅ `useApiSources.ts` exports `getModelsForSource(sourceId)` helper
- ✅ `AgentsConfigView.vue` model selector (`<select v-model="editing.model_id">`) lists all models from selected ApiSource
- ✅ `availableModels` computed uses `getModelsForSource(editing.value.api_source_id)`
- ✅ Watcher on `api_source_id` auto-selects first model + updates model_tier
- ✅ Watcher on `model_id` syncs model_tier from selected model
- ✅ `getModelDisplayName()` shows "Model Name (Tier)" format in card badges
- ✅ No duplicate definitions (verified single definition of each computed/watch/function)
- ✅ i18n: uses `t('agents.model')` for label

### Cosmetic Deviation (Non-blocking)

Tier badge CSS uses subtle/pastel style (low-opacity backgrounds with darker text) instead of spec's bold style (solid backgrounds with white text). Hue values match spec exactly: Min=gray, Lite=green, Mid=blue, Pro=purple, Max=amber. The subtle approach works better with dark mode and does not affect functionality. **No fix required.**

### Bugs Found

None. Implementation is complete and matches design spec.

