### Implementation Verification (Code Review)

- ✅ `AgentConfig` struct has `model_id: String` with `#[serde(default)]` (line ~375)
- ✅ `model_tier: ModelTier` kept with `#[serde(default)]` as deprecated (line ~378)
- ✅ `resolve_model()` uses direct `model_id` lookup, no tier downgrade walk (line ~560)
- ✅ `assign_model_ids()` migrates empty model_id from tier, returns bool for save (line ~540)
- ✅ `generate_default_agents_with_source()` generates empty model_id (line ~460)
- ✅ `load_or_generate_agent_configs()` calls `assign_model_ids()` (line ~510)
- ✅ `assign_model_ids` returns `bool` to track if any migration happened (avoid unnecessary saves)

- ✅ `AgentConfigDto` has `model_id: string` field
- ✅ `model_tier` kept as `'min' | 'lite' | 'mid' | 'pro' | 'max'` for display

- ✅ `getModelsForSource(sourceId)` helper added and exported

- ✅ No duplicate definitions (prior bug reports were stale)
- ✅ `availableModels` computed uses `getModelsForSource(editing.value.api_source_id)`
- ✅ Watcher on `api_source_id` auto-selects first model + updates model_tier
- ✅ Watcher on `model_id` syncs model_tier from selected model
- ✅ Model selector `<select>` lists all models with tier badges
- ✅ i18n: uses `t('agents.model')` for label
- ✅ `getModelDisplayName()` shows "Model Name (Tier)" format in card badges

### CSS Tier Badge Color Verification

Spec: Min=gray, Lite=green, Mid=blue, Pro=purple, Max=amber

Implementation (line ~560):
```css
.tier-badge.min { hsl(0 0% 60%) }    /* gray ✅ */
.tier-badge.lite { hsl(150 55% 42%) } /* green ✅ */
.tier-badge.mid { hsl(210 60% 50%) }  /* blue ✅ */
.tier-badge.pro { hsl(260 55% 52%) }  /* purple ✅ */
.tier-badge.max { hsl(38 92% 50%) }   /* amber ✅ */
```

**Note**: Implementation uses subtle/low-opacity backgrounds (hsl with 0.12 alpha) with darker text instead of spec's bold solid backgrounds with white text. Hue values are correct. This is a cosmetic deviation that works better with dark/light theme toggling.

### Bugs Found

None in this verification pass. All previously reported bugs appear to have been resolved.

