| resolve_model() by model_id | TC-T3.1, TC-T3.2, TC-T3.3, TC-T3.4, TC-T3.5, TC-T3.6, TC-T3.15 |
| Default configs reference model_id | TC-T3.14 |
| Migrations convert tier→model_id | TC-T3.7, TC-T3.8, TC-T3.9, TC-T3.10 |

### Bugs Found

#### BUG-1: Duplicate definitions in AgentsConfigView.vue (compile-breaking)
1. `availableModels` computed property defined **twice** (lines ~210 and ~235)
2. `watch(() => editing.value?.api_source_id, ...)` defined **twice** (lines ~215 and ~240)
3. `watch(() => editing.value?.model_id, ...)` defined **twice** (lines ~225 and ~250)
4. `getModelDisplayName()` function defined **twice** (lines ~230 and ~255)
5. In `startCreate()`, `model_id` key appears **twice** in the same object literal:
   ```typescript
   model_id: '',
   model_id: '',  // duplicate key — TypeScript strict mode error
   ```

## ApiSources-T3 [G3] Model-First Agent Configuration Tests
**Status:** done
**Test File:** `backend/src/relay/config.rs` (inline `#[cfg(test)] mod tests`)
**File:** `frontend/src/views/AgentsConfigView.vue`
**Module:** `backend/src/relay/config.rs`
**Depends on:** ApiSources-G3, ApiSources-D1, ApiSources-P3

### Implementation Status
All 15 test cases are implemented in the existing `#[cfg(test)] mod tests` block at the bottom of `config.rs`. The implementation code (resolve_model, assign_model_ids, generate_default_agents_with_source, AgentConfig with model_id) is also complete.

### Test Cases (all passing)

| Test Case | Description | Status |
|-----------|-------------|--------|
