#### TC-T3.9: assign_model_ids skips configs that already have model_id

```
Given: AgentConfig { model_id: "already-set" }
When:  assign_model_ids()
Then:  model_id remains "already-set"
```

#### TC-T3.10: assign_model_ids handles empty api_sources

```
Given: api_sources = [], config { model_id: "" }
When:  assign_model_ids()
Then:  model_id remains ""
```

#### TC-T3.11: Serde round-trip — old JSON (no model_id) deserializes with defaults

```
Given: JSON: {"id":"test","name":"T","profession_id":"assistant","soul_id":"assistant","api_source_id":"src","model_tier":"mid",...}
When:  serde_json::from_str::(json)
Then:  model_id == "", model_tier == Mid
```

#### TC-T3.12: Serde round-trip — new JSON (with model_id) deserializes correctly

```
Given: JSON with both model_id and model_tier
When:  Deserialized
Then:  Both fields preserve their values
```

#### TC-T3.13: Serde round-trip — new JSON without model_tier uses default

```
Given: JSON with model_id but no model_tier
When:  Deserialized
Then:  model_tier == Min (serde default), model_id preserved
```

#### TC-T3.14: generate_default_agents_with_source produces empty model_id

```
Given: generate_default_agents_with_source("test-source")
Then:  All configs have model_id=="", correct tiers, correct source id
```

#### TC-T3.15: resolve_model preserves all AgentConfig parameters in ModelConfig

```
Given: AgentConfig { temperature: 0.7, max_tokens: 16384, reasoning_budget: Some(8192) }
When:  resolve_model()
Then:  ModelConfig has matching temperature, max_tokens, reasoning_budget
```

