| Model tier becomes display tag only | TC-T3.7, TC-T3.8 (tier used only for migration lookup) |
| Frontend model list selection | Frontend — not testable from Rust unit tests |
| resolve_model() by model_id | TC-T3.1, TC-T3.2, TC-T3.3, TC-T3.4, TC-T3.5, TC-T3.6, TC-T3.15 |
| Default configs reference model_id | TC-T3.14 |
| Migrations convert tier→model_id | TC-T3.7, TC-T3.8, TC-T3.9, TC-T3.10 |

## ApiSources-T3 Model-First Agent Configuration Tests
**Status:** draft
**File:** `backend/src/relay/config.rs`
**Module:** `backend/src/relay/config.rs`
**Depends on:** ApiSources-G3, ApiSources-D1, ApiSources-P3

### Test Cases

#### TC-T3.1: resolve_model with valid model_id returns correct model

```
Given: AgentConfig with model_id="claude-sonnet-4" and api_source_id referencing source with that model
When:  resolve_model() is called
Then:  Returns ModelConfig with model="claude-sonnet-4", correct provider, temperature, max_tokens
```

#### TC-T3.2: resolve_model with invalid model_id falls back to first model

```
Given: AgentConfig with model_id="nonexistent-model" and api_source_id referencing valid source
When:  resolve_model() is called
Then:  Returns ModelConfig with model=first model's id, does not panic or return None
```

#### TC-T3.3: resolve_model with empty model_id falls back to first model

```
Given: AgentConfig with model_id="" (legacy config before migration)
When:  resolve_model() is called
Then:  Returns ModelConfig with model=first model's id (same fallback as invalid)
```

#### TC-T3.4: resolve_model with missing api_source_id falls back to first source

```
Given: AgentConfig with api_source_id="deleted-source" and model_id matching a model in first source
When:  resolve_model() is called with multiple api_sources
Then:  Returns ModelConfig resolved from the first api_source
```

#### TC-T3.5: resolve_model returns None when no api_sources provided

```
Given: AgentConfig with any model_id, api_sources = []
When:  resolve_model() is called
Then:  Returns None
```

#### TC-T3.6: resolve_model returns None when api_source has empty models

```
Given: AgentConfig with valid api_source_id, but that source has models=[]
When:  resolve_model() is called
Then:  Returns None
```

#### TC-T3.7: assign_model_ids migrates tier to model_id

```
Given: AgentConfig with model_id="" and model_tier=Mid, ApiSource with Mid-tier model "claude-sonnet-4"
When:  assign_model_ids() is called
Then:  config.model_id becomes "claude-sonnet-4"
```

#### TC-T3.8: assign_model_ids falls back to first model when tier not found

```
Given: AgentConfig with model_id="" and model_tier=Pro, ApiSource with only Min and Lite models
When:  assign_model_ids() is called
Then:  config.model_id becomes first model's id
```

#### TC-T3.9: assign_model_ids skips configs that already have model_id

```
Given: AgentConfig with model_id="already-set"
When:  assign_model_ids() is called
Then:  config.model_id remains "already-set" (not overwritten)
```

#### TC-T3.10: assign_model_ids handles empty api_sources

```
Given: AgentConfig with model_id="" and model_tier=Mid, api_sources=[]
When:  assign_model_ids() is called
Then:  config.model_id remains "" (cannot migrate)
```

#### TC-T3.11: Serde round-trip: old JSON (no model_id) deserializes with defaults

```
Given: JSON string of AgentConfig without "model_id" field
When:  Deserialized
Then:  model_id == "" (serde default), model_tier preserves original value
```

#### TC-T3.12: Serde round-trip: new JSON (with model_id) deserializes correctly

```
Given: JSON string of AgentConfig with both "model_id" and "model_tier"
When:  Deserialized
Then:  model_id matches JSON value, model_tier matches JSON value
```

#### TC-T3.13: Serde round-trip: new JSON without model_tier deserializes with default

```
Given: JSON string of AgentConfig with "model_id" but no "model_tier"
When:  Deserialized
Then:  model_tier defaults to Min (first variant), model_id preserves value
```

#### TC-T3.14: generate_default_agents_with_source produces empty model_id

```
Given: generate_default_agents_with_source("test-source")
When:  result examined
Then:  all configs have model_id=="", model_tier set per profession, api_source_id=="test-source"
```

#### TC-T3.15: resolve_model preserves all AgentConfig parameters

```
Given: AgentConfig with temperature=0.7, max_tokens=16384, reasoning_budget=Some(8192)
When:  resolve_model() is called
Then:  Returned ModelConfig has matching temperature, max_tokens, reasoning_budget
```

